77 uiderunt is not beyond suspicion, though neitherfinxerunt (Bormans, Unger) nor uicerunt ( Munro) nor luserunt (Baehrens 1) is more than a possible emendation. ‘The poet’s eye’ has become familiar to us from Shakespeare: but the idea was not so common in antiquity.
